@node strlen
@section @code{strlen}---character string length
@findex strlen
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <string.h>
size_t strlen(const char *@var{str});

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
The @code{strlen} function works out the length of the string
starting at @code{*@var{str}} by counting chararacters until it
reaches a @code{NULL} character.

@*
@strong{Returns}@*
@code{strlen} returns the character count.

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
@code{strlen} is ANSI C.

@code{strlen} requires no supporting OS subroutines.

@*
